abstract: The “first in the nation” primary never lets Iowa tell it what to do. Especially not this year.
snippet: The “first in the nation” primary never lets Iowa tell it what to do. Especially not this year.
lead_paragraph: DERRY, N.H. — Throughout the nearly half century-long presidential rivalry between Iowa and New Hampshire, sometimes a state has to dig deep to make its case for why its contest is in fact superior.

abstract: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg's shadow over the Democratic presidential race grew a bit longer on Tuesday after his surprise write-in win in a hamlet that traditionally kicks off voting in New Hampshire's closely watched primary election.

abstract: The Democratic presidential race is deeply unsettled heading into the New Hampshire primary. It may be up to the state to put some structure around the chaotic contest, with Iowa being unable to declare a clear winner.

abstract: New Hampshire has been holding the first-in-the-nation presidential primary for 100 years, but a significant number of Tuesday's ballots could be cast by newcomers to that storied tradition.

abstract: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg, who is not even on the ballot,  won the votes of a tiny New Hampshire community  that barely hung onto its tradition of being among the first to make their picks in the presidential primary.

lead_paragraph: DIXVILLE NOTCH, N.H. — Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg, who is not even on the ballot, won the votes of a tiny New Hampshire community that barely hung onto its tradition of being among the first to make their picks in the presidential primary.
